column11: Localities throughout the West Bank and Gaza Strip were scheduled to hold their first municipal elections since 2012 in October (Associated Press). Those elections were delayed in early September by a court ruling, and the length of that delay remains unclear (Al Jazeera, Associated Press, NY Times). Given the likelihood of an Hamas Victory, the Israelis simply consider that option as a dangerous trend for their country. Maintaining territorial control, and control over the relationship with Abbas, Israelis view this option as the maximized choice M(R, X) :( argmax(X) I X --> X, two dimensional continuous space, with xPy and yPx when argMAX m(R,X) > 0. Consequently, the maximized choice set for Abbas implies that it would be willing to maintain an asymmetrical political relationship in order the successfully foil Hama's preferences regarding territorial control over both occupied geographies along with the political & economic consequences that result from such as maximized choice for Hammas. Abbas therefore will delay elections into the future until he militarily and politically maintains a winning coalition over Hamas.
